author: USA TODAY, Maureen Groppe, USA TODAY

title: As nation reels from Michigan State shooting, courts wrestle with access to guns
description: Pot smokers? Nonviolent felons? After the Supreme Court's landmark ruling on the Second Amendment, lower courts are examining laws on gun possession.
author: USA TODAY, John Fritze, USA TODAY

title: Trump Grand Jury Recommends Perjury Indictments
description: However, it is still unclear if the former president himself will be charged.
author: Greg Walters, Josh Visser

title: Trump Is Closer Than Ever to Being Charged With a Crime
description: Three sets of prosecutors are closing in on the former president. Here’s where each probe stands.
author: Greg Walters, Josh Visser

title: Trump Grand Jury Says Witnesses May Have Lied Under Oath
description: A special purpose grand jury in Georgia that probed the former president’s attempts to reverse his election defeat heard from 75 witnesses. And it’s got concerns.
author: Greg Walters, Josh Visser

title: Mike Pence Could Help Bring the Coup Plotters to Justice
description: But he’s choosing not to.
author: Todd Zwillich, chloe angyal

title: ‘Democracy Is On the Line’ In 2023’s Most Important Election
description: Abortion, voting rights, fair maps, and democracy itself are at stake in a judicial race in Wisconsin, America’s most crucial swing state.
author: Cameron Joseph, chloe angyal

title: Anti-Vaxxers Think It's Time For Political and Legal Revenge
description: Buoyed by the purported end of a pandemic that continues to kill thousands, anti-vaccine activists now vow to punish their enemies. “These people,” said one, “need to go to prison.”
author: Anna Merlan, Tim Marchman

title: Tucker Carlson Called Trump a ‘Demonic Force’ and Other Wild Texts From the Dominion Lawsuit
description: “What he’s good at is destroying things. He’s the undisputed world champion of that. He could easily destroy us if we play it wrong.”
author: David Gilbert, chloe angyal
